data.enText: having a high moral or intellectual level

data.chText: 高尚的语言 / 情操 / 思想

data.enText: higher than the area around; above the level of the ground
data.chText: 高的；升高的；高出地面的

data.enText: The house is in an elevated position, overlooking the town.
data.chText: 这栋房子地势较高，可以俯瞰全城。

data.enText: an elevated highway/railway/road (= one that runs on a bridge above the ground or street)
data.chText: 高架公路 / 铁路 / 道路

means: 提拔，晋升，提升(到不应有的位置)

tr: a railway that is powered by electricity and that runs on a track that is raised above the street level
of high moral or intellectual value
example: argue in terms of high-flown ideals"- Oliver Frank

example.ex: His career has blossomed and that has given him a certain elevated status.
example.tran: 他的事业蓬勃发展，这在一定程度上提升了他的地位。

value.def: A person, job, or role that is elevated is very important or of very high rank.
value.tran: （人、工作、角色等）重要的，地位高的

example.tran: 杂志中高贵的英伦情调

value.def: If thoughts or ideas are elevated, they are on a high moral or intellectual level.
value.tran: （想法、思想等）高尚的，崇高的,睿智的

example.ex: An elevated platform on the stage collapsed during rehearsals.
example.tran: 在排练过程中舞台上垫高的一个平台塌了。

value.def: If land or buildings are elevated, they are raised up higher than the surrounding area.
value.tran: （土地、建筑等）高出周围的，高架的

trans: 真实道路高度；道路高度；高架道路；高架路
